<doc id="14161" url="https://en.wikinews.org/wiki?curid=14161" title="Baseball, softball dropped from 2012 Olympics">
<h1>Baseball, softball dropped from 2012 Olympics</h1>
&lt;strong class="published"&gt;&lt;span id="publishDate" class="value-title" title=""&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class="Z3988" style="display:none" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rfr_id=rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:User%3ADendodge&amp;rft_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:&amp;rft.atitle=Baseball%2C%20softball%20dropped%20from%202012%20Olympics&amp;rft.jtitle=Wikinews&amp;rft.date=&amp;rft.aucorp=Wikinews+contributors&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.rights=CC-BY+2.5&amp;rft.identifier=&amp;rft.artnum="&gt; &lt;/span&gt; 
The &lt;a href="w%3AInternational%20Olympic%20Committee"&gt;International Olympic Committee&lt;/a&gt; has announced today that &lt;a href="w%3Abaseball"&gt;baseball&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="w%3Asoftball"&gt;softball&lt;/a&gt; are to be cut from Olympic competition from &lt;a href="w%3A2012%20Summer%20Olympics"&gt;2012&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href="w%3ARugby"&gt;Rugby&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="w%3Akarate"&gt;karate&lt;/a&gt;, rollersports, &lt;a href="w%3Agolf"&gt;golf&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href="w%3Asquash"&gt;squash&lt;/a&gt; have been rumored to be included. The IOC meets later today to discuss the new Olympic Program.

The vote, held in &lt;a href="w%3ASingapore"&gt;Singapore&lt;/a&gt;, surprised some supporters of the sports, who believed that there were enough votes to retain them.

